  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Band-Resisted Squat uses band tension to train squat pattern using band tension to add ascending resistance and bracing demand.","setup":["Inspect the band for wear and set a secure anchor or foot position before the athlete loads it.","Have the athlete stand on a long band or use a safe low anchor with band tension balanced through the hands or shoulders.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep and rehearse the finish position."],"execution_steps":["Begin from the organized start position for Band-Resisted Squat.","Sit into a controlled squat, keep knees tracking, then stand against increasing band tension.","Move with controlled tempo through the full range the athlete can own.","Reset posture and breath before the next repetition or side."],"coach_cues":["Own the start position.","Control the band; do not let it control you.","Slow where it matters, strong through the finish.","Ribs over pelvis.","Final rep should look like the first.","Knees track with toes.","Brace and breathe."],"athlete_cues":["Stay organized.","Control down.","Strong finish.","Stop before it gets ugly."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale before the hard portion.","Brace without locking the throat.","Exhale through the finish or during the hold without losing shape."],"common_faults":["Chasing more reps or resistance after alignment changes.","Rushing the eccentric or bouncing through the hard range.","Holding the breath for the entire set instead of bracing and breathing.","Changing stance, band path, or trunk position to survive the set.","Using a band that is too heavy or anchored at the wrong angle."],"quality_gate":["No pain.","Start and finish positions match.","Band path or body line stays repeatable.","Final rep or final five seconds stays clean."],"stop_signs":["Pain appears or increases.","Technique changes more than one rep in a row.","Band anchor slips, grip fails, or support surface moves.","Breathing becomes dizziness, panic bracing, or uncontrolled breath holding."]}'::jsonb,
