  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Incline Push-Up uses bodyweight leverage to train regressed push-up pattern that builds pressing strength with adjustable bodyweight load.","setup":["Use a stable box or bench that does not slide and matches the athlete''s current range.","Have the athlete place hands on a stable box or wall with body in a straight line.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep and rehearse the finish position."],"execution_steps":["Begin from the organized start position for Incline Push-Up.","Lower chest toward the support with elbows controlled, then press away while keeping ribs quiet.","Move with controlled tempo through the full range the athlete can own.","Reset posture and breath before the next repetition or side."],"coach_cues":["Own the start position.","Slow where it matters, strong through the finish.","Ribs over pelvis.","Final rep should look like the first.","Push the floor or band away with quiet ribs.","Brace and breathe."],"athlete_cues":["Stay organized.","Control down.","Strong finish.","Stop before it gets ugly."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale before the hard portion.","Brace without locking the throat.","Exhale through the finish or during the hold without losing shape."],"common_faults":["Chasing more reps or resistance after alignment changes.","Rushing the eccentric or bouncing through the hard range.","Holding the breath for the entire set instead of bracing and breathing.","Changing stance, band path, or trunk position to survive the set."],"quality_gate":["No pain.","Start and finish positions match.","Band path or body line stays repeatable.","Final rep or final five seconds stays clean."],"stop_signs":["Pain appears or increases.","Technique changes more than one rep in a row.","Band anchor slips, grip fails, or support surface moves.","Breathing becomes dizziness, panic bracing, or uncontrolled breath holding."]}'::jsonb,
