  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Dead Bug uses bodyweight leverage to train supine anti-extension drill that builds trunk control while arms and legs create leverage.","setup":["Have the athlete lie on the back with arms up, hips and knees at 90 degrees, and low ribs gently down.","Choose a range and resistance level the athlete can own without pain.","Set the brace before the first rep and rehearse the finish position."],"execution_steps":["Begin from the organized start position for Dead Bug.","Reach opposite arm and leg away without arching, breathe, and return with control.","Move with controlled tempo through the full range the athlete can own.","Reset posture and breath before the next repetition or side."],"coach_cues":["Own the start position.","Slow where it matters, strong through the finish.","Ribs over pelvis.","Final rep should look like the first.","Brace and breathe."],"athlete_cues":["Stay organized.","Control down.","Strong finish.","Stop before it gets ugly."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale before the hard portion.","Brace without locking the throat.","Exhale through the finish or during the hold without losing shape."],"common_faults":["Chasing more reps or resistance after alignment changes.","Rushing the eccentric or bouncing through the hard range.","Holding the breath for the entire set instead of bracing and breathing.","Changing stance, band path, or trunk position to survive the set."],"quality_gate":["No pain.","Start and finish positions match.","Band path or body line stays repeatable.","Final rep or final five seconds stays clean."],"stop_signs":["Pain appears or increases.","Technique changes more than one rep in a row.","Band anchor slips, grip fails, or support surface moves.","Breathing becomes dizziness, panic bracing, or uncontrolled breath holding."]}'::jsonb,
